<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 27 at 3:45PM EDT  by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg</headline>
<description>...Strong thunderstorms will impact portions of western Alexander and
eastern Caldwell Counties through 415 PM EDT...
At 345 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 9 miles west of Boomer to 4 miles southwest of
Lenoir. Movement was east at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Lenoir, Taylorsville, Sawmills, Granite Falls, Gamewell, Bethlehem,
Hudson, Cajah`s Mountain, Rhodhiss and Cedar Rock.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
